<task id="036" project="ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>`GateApprovalCard` Fluent v9 component in `Spaarke.UI.Components` (ADR-021 dark-mode tested); used by `InteractiveInChatGateResolver` and SpaarkeAi</title>
    <phase>Phase 3: IGateResolver + Approval Surface</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>6</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>030</dependencies>
    <blocks>050, 062</blocks>
    <tags>pcf, react, fluent-ui, frontend</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Implements canonical shared UI component for approval surface used across Spaarke (SpaarkeAi + future Teams/M365 Copilot); modifies `.tsx` files in shared component library; tags include pcf/react/fluent-ui/frontend; ADR-021 dark-mode test required; UI tests defined</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Different surface (`Spaarke.UI.Components` package, not `Sprk.Bff.Api`); no file overlap with Group D BFF resolver tasks (031–034); safe to run alongside Group D — consumes only the SSE event vocabulary contract defined in task 030 + 032's `notes/decisions/032-sse-gate-events.md`</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Build `GateApprovalCard` Fluent UI v9 component at `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/GateApprovalCard/` (new folder). Render gate-request details (gate type, summary, payload preview, approver-role hint, countdown timer for 5-min timeout) and provide Approve/Reject controls with optional rejection reason. Exports via `src/index.ts`. Used by `InteractiveInChatGateResolver` (SpaarkeAi surface in Phase 5) and future Teams/M365 Copilot surfaces. MUST use Fluent v9 semantic tokens (ADR-021 dark-mode tested). MUST be stateless from data fetching — props-driven, with `onApprove` + `onReject` callbacks.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior Spaarke frontend engineer with Fluent UI v9 + React 18 expertise. You build accessible, dark-mode-compliant, semantically-tokenized components. You separate presentation from data fetching — the card is purely props-driven so any host (chat panel, Teams card, M365 Copilot) can mount it without coupling to the SSE channel.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Concrete deliverables:
    1. **`GateApprovalCard` component** — props: `gateRequest: GateCardProps` (correlationId, gateType, summary, payloadPreview, authorizedApproverRoles, surfaceHint, timeoutSeconds, requestedByDisplayName), `onApprove: () =&gt; void | Promise&lt;void&gt;`, `onReject: (reason: string) =&gt; void | Promise&lt;void&gt;`, `disabled?: boolean`, `className?: string`.
    2. **Countdown timer** — visible countdown of remaining seconds; styled to indicate urgency (color shift &lt;60 sec). Pure visual; the resolver enforces the actual timeout server-side per task 035.
    3. **Reject-with-reason flow** — clicking Reject opens an inline `Textarea` for optional reason; submit fires `onReject(reason)`.
    4. **Dark mode** — uses `tokens.colorNeutralBackground*`, `tokens.colorNeutralForeground*`, etc. NO hardcoded colors. Tested under both themes (ADR-021).
    5. **Storybook story** (if Storybook exists in `Spaarke.UI.Components`; else stub component example) — variants: default, near-timeout, dark mode, disabled.
    6. **Unit tests** (Jest + React Testing Library) — render assertions, click handlers, accessibility.
    7. **Export** via `src/index.ts` so consumers (`@spaarke/ui-components`) can `import { GateApprovalCard } from '@spaarke/ui-components'`.
    8. **TypeScript types** — `GateCardProps` exported alongside the component; mirror server-side `GateRequest` field names where consumer-facing.
    9. **UI tests** (executed by `task-execute` Step 9.7 via `ui-test` skill against deployed SpaarkeAi).

    Deliverable locations:
    - `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/GateApprovalCard/GateApprovalCard.tsx`
    - `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/GateApprovalCard/GateApprovalCard.types.ts`
    - `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/GateApprovalCard/GateApprovalCard.styles.ts`
    - `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/GateApprovalCard/index.ts`
    - `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/GateApprovalCard/GateApprovalCard.test.tsx`
    - `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/index.ts` (export added)
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per design §5 and spec FR-17, `GateApprovalCard` is the canonical approval-surface UI primitive across Spaarke. Surfaces consuming it: SpaarkeAi (Phase 5 — primary MVP consumer), Teams cards (R2), M365 Copilot (R3), Insights Engine Precedent Board (R2 — see coordination assessment §4.6).

      The component is intentionally STATELESS from data fetching:
      - The hosting surface fetches gate state (via SSE event in SpaarkeAi, via Teams card payload, etc.).
      - The hosting surface invokes server actions (POST `/api/ai/gates/in-chat/respond` for SpaarkeAi; Teams bot action for Teams).
      - The component renders + emits user intent.

      ADR-021 dark-mode parity is non-negotiable. Every visual element uses Fluent v9 semantic tokens; no `#hexcode` or `rgb(...)` literals.

      The `notes/decisions/032-sse-gate-events.md` (from task 032) documents the SSE event payload that SpaarkeAi parses to populate `GateCardProps`. Coordinate that contract.
    </background>
