  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-006">UI Surface Architecture. Code Page (SpaarkeAi) hosts the card; shared component library is the home.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-011">Component library conventions (if applicable to project). Use shared component patterns per `Spaarke.UI.Components` conventions.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Shared component library. `GateApprovalCard` MUST live in `Spaarke.UI.Components`; MUST use Fluent UI v9; MUST NOT reference PCF-specific APIs (consumable from any React 18 host).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent UI v9 + dark mode. Semantic tokens only. Dark-mode parity tested.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Stateless from data fetching: props-driven, with `onApprove` + `onReject` callbacks. Hosting surface owns the data flow.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Countdown timer is purely visual; server-side `GateTimeoutService` (task 035) enforces actual timeout.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">SSE event vocabulary defined in `notes/decisions/032-sse-gate-events.md` — the card's `GateCardProps` shape MUST be parseable from that payload.</constraint>
  </constraints>

