  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Pure props-driven design is the load-bearing decision. If `GateApprovalCard` reaches into an SSE channel or service, it stops being reusable across surfaces (Teams, M365 Copilot). Hosting surfaces own the data flow; the card owns the visual + interaction contract.

    The TypeScript `GateCardProps` mirrors the server-side `GateRequest` fields in shape but uses camelCase (TS convention) vs PascalCase (C# convention). Document this in `notes/decisions/036-gateapprovalcard-props-contract.md` to avoid future inconsistency.

    Phase 5 task 050 (SpaarkeAi card mount) wires SSE event → props mapping. Phase 6 task 062 (UI integration tests) executes the `&lt;ui-tests&gt;` defined here against deployed SpaarkeAi.

    Bundle-size budget for `Spaarke.UI.Components` is tracked in the package's CI; check `package.json` `size-limit` config if present. If unclear, document the actual measured bundle delta in PR description.

    Storybook is OPTIONAL for this task — if Storybook is not already wired in `Spaarke.UI.Components`, skip and document in the notes. Do not introduce Storybook scaffolding here (out of scope).
  </notes>

